features.text:
The metaphysicians of Uqbar, known for their distinctive masks and horns, are descended from an ancient culture that spent several thousand years in isolation, resulting in the discovery of The Arts of alchemy and astrology. The equipment used by modern-day metaphysicians combines more recent technology with these metaphysical principles, sometimes with devastating effects; however, the metaphysicians are well aware that sacrifice is required to fight against the Offspring of Anu, in their eternal, secret war.
Metaphysicians are selected from the population at a young age by sages from the Academy of Metaphysics; a masksmith then creates a completely unique mask for the initiate, based on their intricate astrological qualities. It is rumored that the mask becomes physically attached to the face, preventing the metaphysician from ever removing it and symbolizing the fact that for a newly-initiated metaphysician, there is no going back, physically or otherwise.
A metaphysician spends much of their life going through the intense training regimen of the Academy, and depending on the metaphysician's specific field of study, it can even take their entire life; for instance, those who are called to explore the secrets of the brain and consciousness have been known to go mad, not from the stress of their studies, but from the studied content itself. Many banned, forgotten, or supposedly lost books can be found within the Academy, kept hidden and safe from those not capable of handling the deeply troubling information found within these tomes.
